What's it like to be young, homeless and struggling in a town where one in four households are on benefit? Panorama investigates.

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/07/28/06f2e2596881c73c8e5e815f7f447a66.png[/img]

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/07/28/0d6a1ddf740d4a71e7e5cc768c194f2b.jpg[/img]

What's life like to be young, homeless and struggling in a town where one in four households are on benefit? Panorama has spent four weeks filming with the young residents of the YMCA in Stoke, once home to some of the world's greatest potteries. The YMCA in England and Wales provides accommodation and support to just under 10,000 16-25 year olds but fears its services may be under threat by the government's proposed cuts to housing benefit
